and live diligently till the end.

794
00:59:57,855 --> 01:00:00,427
If I knew this was going to happen,

795
01:00:00,547 --> 01:00:05,216
I should have let Ah Ran and Joo Seung
leave at the beginning.

796
01:00:06,731 --> 01:00:08,778
Why was I,

797
01:00:08,898 --> 01:00:11,426
so insistent on my revenge?

798
01:00:12,462 --> 01:00:14,228
Unni.

799
01:00:14,641 --> 01:00:16,124
Go well.

800
01:00:19,251 --> 01:00:21,467
In our next lives,

801
01:00:22,275 --> 01:00:24,622
be my Unni again.

802
01:00:25,996 --> 01:00:28,043
Then...

803
01:00:29,658 --> 01:00:31,742
let's not separate,

804
01:00:33,057 --> 01:00:35,179
and not hate each other,

805
01:00:38,158 --> 01:00:39,980
and not fight.

806
01:01:03,568 --> 01:01:05,108
<i>Ah Ran,</i>

807
01:01:06,237 --> 01:01:09,430
<i>didn't want me to tell you
for the time being.</i>

808
01:01:18,632 --> 01:01:20,548
The death report.

809
01:01:21,564 --> 01:01:25,320
Why would Unni file a death
report for Joo Kyeong Ran?

810
01:01:25,440 --> 01:01:29,564
She wanted you to live under
the name of Yun Jae Hee in the future.

811
01:01:31,407 --> 01:01:33,210
So in that case, there would
be no problem if you wanted

812
01:01:35,032 --> 01:01:37,248
to marry Teacher Shin.

813
01:01:59,021 --> 01:02:00,242
What?

814
01:02:00,362 --> 01:02:02,007
What does that mean?

815
01:02:02,127 --> 01:02:04,589
Mother asked to look at the brake?

816
01:02:04,709 --> 01:02:08,815
She came to our auto club,
and asked to take apart the brake.

817
01:02:09,212 --> 01:02:13,456
Then, everything was fine,
and the accident happened.

818
01:02:23,869 --> 01:02:25,785
Could it be...

819
01:02:43,040 --> 01:02:44,936
<i>Joo Seung.</i>

820
01:02:45,056 --> 01:02:49,349
<i>Every year when I received
a birthday present from you,</i>

821
01:02:49,469 --> 01:02:53,753
<i>I shamelessly anticipated it, and was happy.</i>

822
01:02:55,124 --> 01:02:58,316
<i>There wasn't one I didn't like.</i>

823
01:02:59,137 --> 01:03:01,034
<i>The pearl necklace you sent me,</i>

824
01:03:01,154 --> 01:03:02,912
<i>the scarf,</i>

825
01:03:03,032 --> 01:03:04,978
<i>the blouse.</i>

826
01:03:05,672 --> 01:03:08,921
<i>They were all so precious,
thank you very much.</i>

827
01:03:10,880 --> 01:03:12,890
<i>All the crimes I committed,</i>

828
01:03:13,010 --> 01:03:15,406
<i>I'll take them away.</i>

829
01:03:16,683 --> 01:03:21,635
<i>Forgive, the Mum that only left you pain.</i>

830
01:03:23,682 --> 01:03:26,818
<i>But in this last moment before I leave,</i>

831
01:03:28,114 --> 01:03:31,232
<i>I've never regretted giving birth to you.</i>

832
01:03:31,663 --> 01:03:34,236
<i>Father, Hyung and younger brother,</i>

833
01:03:35,043 --> 01:03:38,799
<i>are the last presents I leave for you.</i>

834
01:03:49,072 --> 01:03:50,556
Then,

835
01:03:54,400 --> 01:03:55,715
Mum...

836
01:03:56,879 --> 01:03:58,175
She...

837
01:04:04,483 --> 01:04:05,986
Ah Ran...

838
01:04:20,774 --> 01:04:22,164
Ah Ran...

839
01:04:51,327 --> 01:04:57,130
<i>1 year later</i>

840
01:05:12,195 --> 01:05:13,866
Unni.

841
01:05:14,936 --> 01:05:16,889
Have you been well?

842
01:05:17,453 --> 01:05:19,594
You haven't been cold, right?

843
01:05:20,476 --> 01:05:22,486
I know you miss me,

844
01:05:23,023 --> 01:05:25,295
so I brought a photograph.

845
01:05:41,965 --> 01:05:43,599
It's been a while.

846
01:05:43,719 --> 01:05:45,684
Have you been well?

847
01:05:46,247 --> 01:05:48,050
Yes, Ahjussi.

848
01:05:48,170 --> 01:05:49,552
No,

849
01:05:49,672 --> 01:05:52,106
what about you, President?

850
01:05:52,226 --> 01:05:55,409
I've been really busy, I have no energy.

851
01:05:56,761 --> 01:05:59,409
Occasionally, I see the news in the papers,

852
01:05:59,529 --> 01:06:02,113
congratulations on your big expansion in SM.

853
01:06:02,687 --> 01:06:06,593
Madam, today is her death
anniversary, right?

854
01:06:06,713 --> 01:06:07,983
Yes.

855
01:06:10,163 --> 01:06:12,680
You don't know the news
about Joo Seung, right?

856
01:06:12,800 --> 01:06:15,910
He seems like he's still travelling around.

857
01:06:17,377 --> 01:06:21,340
Once in a while, he sends a postcard
so I won't forget him.

858
01:06:22,035 --> 01:06:24,964
I told him he had to come home
for Mum's death anniversary,

859
01:06:25,084 --> 01:06:26,467
I don't know.

860
01:06:28,434 --> 01:06:33,072
Losing the two people he loved
the most in one day,

861
01:06:34,124 --> 01:06:37,335
that pain, won't disappear so easily.

862
01:06:38,283 --> 01:06:39,597
Right.

863
01:06:39,717 --> 01:06:42,583
I applied for the name,

864
01:06:42,703 --> 01:06:44,405
Joo Kyeong Ran.

865
01:06:46,733 --> 01:06:48,161
Is that so?

866
01:06:49,364 --> 01:06:50,829
Good job.

867
01:06:55,899 --> 01:06:57,796
Then, I'm going to leave.

868
01:06:57,916 --> 01:06:59,815
Director is sick.

869
01:06:59,935 --> 01:07:02,951
I have to cook for the children.

870
01:08:44,163 --> 01:08:46,191
<i>Like a snowflake floating towards you,</i>

871
01:08:46,311 --> 01:08:48,313
<i>don't hesitate, don't stop.</i>

872
01:08:48,433 --> 01:08:49,891
<i>Don't hide.</i>

873
01:08:50,011 --> 01:08:52,042
<i>I want to float into your arms,</i>

874
01:08:52,162 --> 01:08:55,448
<i>and become part of a snowdrift,
an everlasting snowdrift.</i>

875
01:08:57,946 --> 01:08:59,486
<i>There,</i>

876
01:09:00,469 --> 01:09:03,417
<i>are the two people I occasionally protect,</i>

877
01:09:05,239 --> 01:09:07,286
<i>One is my wife.</i>

878
01:09:07,887 --> 01:09:10,441
<i>One is my mother's son.</i>

879
01:09:11,892 --> 01:09:14,145
<i>One person is dead,</i>

880
01:09:14,840 --> 01:09:17,112
<i>one person is tragic.</i>

881
01:09:19,065 --> 01:09:22,652
<i>But why am I not happy right now?</i>

882
01:09:24,572 --> 01:09:27,989
<i>If I had handed the crimes
of those two people to God,</i>

883
01:09:28,722 --> 01:09:31,050
<i>would our lives be different?</i>

884
01:09:32,698 --> 01:09:34,407
<i>Joo Ah Ran,</i>

885
01:09:34,527 --> 01:09:36,153
<i>you've won.</i>

886
01:09:36,979 --> 01:09:41,486
<i>Because, the last person who cut
off the tail of your revenge was me.</i>

887
01:09:43,290 --> 01:09:45,450
<i>My mother's crimes,</i>

888
01:09:46,032 --> 01:09:48,680
<i>for forgiving them before you left,</i>

889
01:09:49,130 --> 01:09:50,689
<i>thank you.</i>